cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG. 

The paper introduces a manual annotation tool for images, audio, and video, which is primarily used in computer vision tasks such as object detection, segmentation, and tracking. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The tool also supports collaborative annotation, which suggests a possible fit with sub-categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The annotations can be exported to plain text data formats, which could be used for further processing and analysis, indicating a possible fit with sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
